 :tx/rationale "DAEMON-W3: Remove RFL-2 action recording from main.rs LiveStore to prevent stale overwrite. PROBLEM: main.rs:201-256 writes RFL-2 action prediction datoms to the main.rs LiveStore L1 after command dispatch. This makes L1 dirty. When L1 drops after the command's L2, L1's flush overwrites L2's correct store.bin with stale state. This is the specific trigger that causes the stale cache overwrite. SOLUTION: (1) When the command was daemon-routed, skip RFL-2 entirely in main.rs — the daemon's handle_with_observation() already records runtime datoms (INV-DAEMON-003). (2) When in direct mode (daemon not running), RFL-2 is still needed but should write to the COMMAND'S LiveStore, not main.rs's. Pass a flag or handle through the command dispatch. (3) Simplest approach: if try_route_through_daemon returned Some (daemon handled it), skip ALL post-hooks. The daemon is responsible for all side effects. VERIFICATION: (1) After daemon-routed observe, main.rs LiveStore.is_dirty() == false. (2) RFL-2 datoms still recorded (by daemon) — query for :action/* entities succeeds. (3) In direct mode, RFL-2 still works (main.rs handles it). FILES: main.rs (~30 LOC). DEPENDS-ON: DAEMON-W2 (routing must work first). BLOCKS: Wave 4 (verification)."
